-- Poland's BZ WBK says 2 bln zlotys 2014 net profit possible
-- By Marcin Goclowski
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 05:38AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, July 31 (Reuters) - Bank Zachodni WBK <BZW.WA>, Poland's No.3 lender and local Banco Santander <SAN.MC> unit, sees 2 billion zlotys ($644 million) as a possible net profit level this year, the bank's Chief Executive Officer Mateusz Morawiecki said on Thursday.

